This workflow retrieves all the child components from the list of component ids.

Inputs\:

artifactIds		- List of component ids each separated by "," for which the child components will be retrieved
userIdentifier	- User Identifier to pass to the wrapper flow to retrieve the child components

Responses\:
success - Workflow completed successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.

The purpose of a target is to define the set of machines to which an application will be deployed. Inputs\: saHost - the host running DA that you want to connect to username - user name to use when connecting to DA password - the password to use when connecting to DA admEnvironment - ADM Name of ADM Application Environment. admTarget - ADM Name of ADM Application Target. appTierServerMapping - pipe "|" separated list of comma "," separated values of application tier and mapping target server. For ex\:Tier1,server1|tier2,server2 -> where server1 maps to Tier1 and server2 maps to Tier2 Responses\: success - if the command completes execution and its exit code is 0 failure - otherwise 6d36faa0-e75d-4b13-b5c9-22e609506592.da09f8ab-35f2-4d75-b43c-363597eccf0a.prompt=ADM Name of ADM Application Version. 6d36faa0-e75d-4b13-b5c9-22e609506592.description=
Create Target, add host into tiers and deploy application

Inputs Parameters\:

 CSA_CONTEXT_ID – CSA Context Id
 CSA_PROCESS_ID – CSA Process Instance Id
 SVC_COMPONENT_ID - This token will resolve to the Service component Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\:SVC_COMPONENT_ID]
 RSC_PROVIDER_ID - This token will resolve to the Resource Provider Id that was selected at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\:RSC_PROVIDER_ID]
 SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_EMAIL - This token will resolve to the subscriber’s email address. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_EMAIL]
 RSC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID - This token will resolve to the Resource subscription Id that was created from the Resource Offering at the Subscription time.
  		Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID]
 SVC_COMPONENT_TYPE - This token will resolve to the Service component type. Eg\: Server.. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_COMPONENT_TYPE]
 RSC_POOL_ID - This token will resolve to the Resource pool Id that was selected at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_POOL_ID]
 SVC_INSTANCE_ID - This token will resolve to the Service Instance Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_INSTANCE_ID]
 SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID - This token will resolve to the Subscription Id that was created at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID]
 PRN_COMPONENT_ID – This token will resolve to the parent Component’s Service Component Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: PRN_COMPONENT_ID]
 REQ_ORG_ID - This token will resolve to the Organization Id associated with the service request. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: REQ_ORG_ID]
 REQ_USER_ID - This token will resolve to the User Id associated with the service request. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: REQ_USER_ID]
 USR_ORG_ID - This token will resolve to the Organization Id associated with the subscriber. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: USR_ORG_ID]
 RSC_BINDING_ID - This token will resolve to the Resource Binding Id that was created at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_BINDING_ID]

Responses\:
 success - The operation completed successfully.
 failure - Something went wrong.
6d36faa0-e75d-4b13-b5c9-22e609506592.e784924e-ddfa-4bf0-801e-dd533fb2b71b.prompt=Process Instance ID 6d36faa0-e75d-4b13-b5c9-22e609506592.eca4e838-e98d-4486-b71b-7a53d258bb1e.description=This operation deploys the given Application's Version on the required target. It will return the details of DeploymentJob created for deploying the version. This Operation is supported for SA 9.0 or later. Inputs\: coreHost - IP Address or DNS name of the SA Web Service. corePort - HTTP(S) port of SA Web Service. By default it is '443' coreProtocol - HTTP / HTTPS. By default it is 'HTTPS' coreUsername - Username of the SA. corePassword - Password of SA user. coreVersion - [Optional] By default, it is the SA version being used. admApplication - ADM Name of ADM Application. admRelease - ADM Name of ADM Application Release. admVersion - ADM Name of ADM Application Version. admEnvironment - ADM Name of ADM Application Environment. admTarget - ADM Name of ADM Application Target. isAdmUndeployPreVersion - [Optional] Should the ADM undeploy the previous version of application? (y/n) By default it is 'y' timeout - [Optional] Job timeout in millisecond, If it is zero (0) then the given operation will return immediately. By default it is '20000' admJobComment - [Optional] Job Comment. Outputs\: status - Operation completion Status. idAdmDeploymentJob - ADM Id of Application Deployment job. admJobStatus - Status of Job. It could be one of [NOT_STARTED, CANCEL_PENDING, CANCELED, PAUSE_PENDING, PAUSED, IN_PROGRESS, COMPLETED, FAILED, ATTENTION_REQUIRED]. admJobComment - Job Comment. isAdmJobRollbacked - Is rollbacked? (y/n). isAdmJobUndeployed - Is Undeployed? (y/n) idAdmRollbackedJob - ADM id of Rollback Job. idAdmUndeployedJob - ADM id of Undeployed Job. admJobStagedDate - Application staged date. (yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH\:mm\:ss.SSSZ). Is available only for SA 9. admJobDeployedDate - Application deployed date. (yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH\:mm\:ss.SSSZ). admJobType - Type of Job. It could be one of [DEPLOYMENT, MAKE_VERSION, ROLLBACK, UNDEPLOYMENT]. idSaJob - SA Id Of SA Job. idAdmVersion - ADM Id of Application Version. admVersion - ADM Name of ADM Application Version. idAdmRelease - ADM Id of Application Release. admRelease - ADM Name of ADM Application Release. idAdmApplication - ADM Id of Application. admApplication - ADM Name of ADM Application. idAdmTarget - ADM Id of Application Target. admTarget - ADM Name of ADM Application Target. idAdmEnvironment - ADM Id of Application Environment. admEnvironment - ADM Name of ADM Application Environment. Responses\: success - Operation passed. For more details, see the output parameter 'status'. failure - Operation failed.
